---
Background:

Consider a periodic chain of length $L$ of Rydberg atoms described by the Hamiltonian
\begin{equation}
    \hat{H} = 
    \sum_j\left[\frac{\Omega}{2}(\hat{b}_j+\hat{b}_j^\dagger)-\Delta \hat{n}_j + V_1\hat{n}_j\hat{n}_{j+1} + V_2 \hat{n}_j\hat{n}_{j+2}\right],
\end{equation}
where $\hat{b}_j$ is a hard-core boson operator, $\hat{n}_j = \hat{b}_j^\dagger \hat{b}_j$ is the number operator with eigenvalues $0$ and $1$, and $V_1 \gg \Omega, \Delta, V_2 > 0$ imposes the Rydberg blockade constraint: no two neighboring atoms can be simultaneously excited.

At criticality, for appropriate $V_2$, the ground state $\ket{\psi_c}$ corresponds to the tricritical Ising (TCI) point, described by a conformal field theory (CFT) with central charge $c=7/10$. In this state, correlations of a microscopic order parameter operator
\begin{equation}
    \hat{\sigma}_{j+1/2} = (-1)^j \frac{\hat{n}_j - \hat{n}_{j+1}}{2}
\end{equation}
exhibit algebraic decay governed by the CFT "spin" field $\sigma$, with scaling dimension $\Delta_\sigma = 3/40$:
\begin{equation}
    \braket{\hat{\sigma}_{\ell_1}\hat{\sigma}_{\ell_2}}_c \sim |\ell_1 - \ell_2|^{-2\Delta_\sigma}
\end{equation}
(where the subscript $c$ denotes connected correlators).

Now, consider the effect of projectively measuring every fourth site, $\{j = 4k\}$ with $k=0,1,\ldots$, and post-selecting for the outcome $n_{4k}=1$ on all measured sites (with all other site occupations left unmeasured). The post-measurement (unnormalized) state is
\begin{equation}
	|\psi_c^{\mathbf{n}}\rangle = \prod_{k}|1_{4k}\rangle\langle 1_{4k}| \psi_c\rangle.
\end{equation}

After this measurement protocol, the order-parameter correlations are again described by
\begin{equation}
    \langle \hat{\sigma}_{{\ell}_1}^{\mathbf{n}}\hat{\sigma}_{{\ell}_2}^{\mathbf{n}}\rangle_c  \sim |{\ell}_1-{\ell}_2|^{-2\Delta'_\sigma},
\end{equation}
where the appropriate microscopic operator $\hat{\sigma}_{\ell}^{\mathbf{n}}$ is the average of $(-1)^j \hat{n}_j$ over the unmeasured sites within each unit cell of the post-measurement pattern, as specified by
\begin{equation}
  \hat{\sigma}_{\ell}^{\mathbf{n}} = \frac{1}{3}\sum_{k = 1}^3 (-1)^{4\ell + k} \hat{n}_{4\ell+k},
\end{equation}
with $\ell$ labeling unit cells.

Task:

In this setting, analytically derive the *exact* scaling dimension $\Delta'_\sigma$ that governs the post-measurement two-point function $\langle \hat{\sigma}_{{\ell}_1}^{\mathbf{n}}\hat{\sigma}_{{\ell}_2}^{\mathbf{n}}\rangle_c$ at the TCI point after the projective measurement protocol described above (measurement and post-selection on every $4$th site with outcome $n_{4k}=1$). Express your answer for $\Delta'_\sigma$ as a number.

