---
Background:

Let $q$ be a complex parameter not a root of unity, and define the $q$-Pochhammer symbol as $(x)_n = \prod_{i=1}^n (1-xq^{i-1})$. The reduced Askey--Wilson polynomials are defined via
\[
P_n(x; x_0, x_1) = (-1)^n q^{-n/2} \frac{(q,\frac{q}{x_0^2},\frac{q}{x_1^2})_n}{(\frac{q^{n+1}}{x_0^2 x_1^2})_n} \sum_{k=0}^n q^k \frac{(q^{-n}, \frac{q^{n+1}}{x_0^2 x_1^2})_k}{(q, q, \frac{q}{x_0^2}, \frac{q}{x_1^2})_k} g_k(x),
\]
where $g_k(x) = (-q^{1/2} x, -q^{1/2} x^{-1})_k$ is a symmetric Laurent polynomial basis.

Define the normalization function
\[
\nu_n(x_0,x_1) = (-1)^n q^{-\frac{1}{2}n(n+1)} \left(  \frac{q^{n+1}}{x_0^2 x_1^2}\right)_n \left(  \frac{q^{n+1}}{x_0^2 x_1^2}\right)_{n+1} \prod_{b=0,1}
  \frac{
    x_b^{\frac{1}{2}} \exp\left(\pi \mathrm{i} \frac{\log x_b}{\log q}\right)
    }{
    \left(\frac{1}{x_b^2}\right)_{n+1}
    \left(\frac{q}{x_b^2}\right)_{n}
    (x_b^2)_\infty
  }.
\]
Let $\bar{P}_n(x; x_0, x_1) = \nu_n(x_0, x_1) P_n(x; x_0, x_1)$.

Define the DAHA $q$-difference operator associated to the genus-two skein module as
\[
\begin{aligned}
\mathcal{A}(\mathbb{k}_6)\, \bar{P}_n(x;x_0,x_1) = 
& \ \bar{P}_{n+1}(x;x_0,x_1) + \frac{(1-q^n)^2\, (1-x_0^2 x_1^2 q^{-n+1})^2}{ (1-x_0^2)(1-q x_0^2)(1-x_1^2)(1-q x_1^2)} \, \bar{P}_{n-1}(x;x_0,x_1)\\
&- \left( \frac{q^{n+\frac{1}{2}} (1-x_0^2 q^{-n})^2}{ (1-x_0^2)(1-q x_0^2)} + \frac{q^{n+\frac{1}{2}} (1-x_1^2 q^{-n})^2}{ (1-x_1^2)(1-q x_1^2)}\right) \bar{P}_n(x;x_0,x_1).
\end{aligned}
\]

Task:

Starting from the definitions above, explicitly derive the expression for $\mathcal{A}(\mathbb{k}_6)\, \bar{P}_n(x;x_0,x_1)$ as a linear combination of $\bar{P}_{n+1}$, $\bar{P}_n$, and $\bar{P}_{n-1}$, with all coefficients given as explicit rational functions of $q$, $n$, $x_0$, $x_1$, as shown above. That is, rederive the full three-term recurrence for the genus-two DAHA action associated to $\mathbb{k}_6$ acting on the reduced Askey--Wilson polynomial with the explicit normalization $\nu_n(x_0, x_1)$.

