problems.problem_statement:
---
Background:  

Consider a finite element model for the corneal stroma in which the tissue microstructure is represented by two classes of truss elements (generalized collagen fibrils and proteoglycan crosslinks) embedded within a continuum solid element that represents the isotropic extracellular matrix (ECM). Each truss is modeled as a one-dimensional hyperelastic body with finite kinematics and volume-preserving deformation. The stretch of a truss is $\lambda = l/L$, where $l$ is the current length and $L$ the reference length. The first Piola-Kirchhoff stress for a truss is $P(\lambda) = \frac{\partial\psi}{\partial\lambda}$, and the scalar tangent stiffness is $\mathcal{A}(\lambda) = \frac{\partial^2\psi}{\partial\lambda^2}$, where $\psi(\lambda)$ is the stored energy per unit reference volume.

For a two-node truss element with nodes $\{\mathrm{a}, \mathrm{b}\}$, the internal nodal forces are
\[
\mathbf{T}_\mathrm{a} = -P(\lambda)A\mathbf{n},\quad \mathbf{T}_\mathrm{b} = P(\lambda)A\mathbf{n}
\]
where $A$ is the reference cross-sectional area, and $\mathbf{n} = (\mathbf{x}_\mathrm{b} - \mathbf{x}_\mathrm{a})/l$ is the unit vector along the truss in the deformed configuration.

Define the element tangent stiffness matrix $\mathbf{K}$ such that
\[
\begin{bmatrix}
\mathbf{T}_\mathrm{a} \\ \mathbf{T}_\mathrm{b}
\end{bmatrix}
= 
\begin{bmatrix}
\mathbf{K}_{\mathrm{aa}} & \mathbf{K}_{\mathrm{ab}} \\
\mathbf{K}_{\mathrm{ba}} & \mathbf{K}_{\mathrm{bb}} \\
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
\mathbf{u}_\mathrm{a} \\ \mathbf{u}_\mathrm{b}
\end{bmatrix}
\]
(where $\mathbf{u}_\mathrm{a}$, $\mathbf{u}_\mathrm{b}$ are nodal displacements) and let $(\mathbf{n}\otimes\mathbf{n})$ denote the second-order unit structural tensor.

Task:

Derive the explicit analytical expressions for the submatrices $\mathbf{K}_{\mathrm{aa}}$ and $\mathbf{K}_{\mathrm{ab}}$ of the tangent stiffness matrix for this nonlinear large-deformation truss, in terms of $\lambda$, $A$, $L$, $l$, $P(\lambda)$, and $\mathcal{A}(\lambda)$, and identify the definitions of any additional scalar factors that appear.

