---
Background:

Consider a two-dimensional quantum spin system on a square lattice with lattice constant $a$, described by the Hamiltonian
\begin{equation*}
H = \sum_{i,j \in \Lambda} J_{ij} \v{S}_i \cdot \v{S}_j,
\end{equation*}
where $\Lambda$ labels the lattice sites, and the spin operators $\v{S}_i$ obey $|\v{S}_i| = S$. The interaction is of two types: nearest-neighbor (NN) exchange $J$, and next-nearest-neighbor (NNN) exchange $J'$ with an additional real parameter $\gamma$, such that the NNN couplings are
\begin{equation*}
J_{i,i\pm\bm{\delta}} = - J' \Big[1 + \sign(\hat{\bm{\delta}})(-1)^i\gamma\Big],
