t}$, $\{\zh_k\}_{k=2}^{
h}$, $\len_\gamma$, and $ eta_\gamma$, eliminating $\zt_1$ and $\zh_1$ via the constraints on their sums. Express the symplectic form as a sum of differential forms (wedge products), with coefficients written in terms of the given $c$-coefficients.

